index 000000000000..ab3f461e0f2d
--- /dev/null
+++ b/Tools/MiniBrowser/common/README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,41 @@
+# MiniBrowser Tab Surface
+
+`TabbedBrowsingModel` is the shared state layer for MiniBrowser tabbed browsing.
+It intentionally has no platform UI dependencies.
+
+The model owns:
+
+- stable tab IDs
+- selection
+- URL, title, loading, back/forward state
+- pinned-tab ordering
+- attention state
+- horizontal vs vertical tab mode
+- vertical tab collapse and width state
+
+Platform code owns:
+
+- Win32 toolbar/sidebar rendering
+- AppKit toolbar/sidebar rendering
+- WPE/Android rendering
+- native accelerators and context menus
+- creating, hiding, showing, and destroying actual web views
+
+Vertical tabs follow Chromium's useful split between tab collection state and
+per-window vertical-strip state. The model exposes the state; each platform is
+free to draw either a horizontal strip or a vertical strip from the same data.
+
+## Later: Extension UI
+
+After tabbed browsing is stable, add the product-owned extension surfaces on top
+of this model:
+
+- extension action button state per active tab
+- popup host anchoring to horizontal and vertical tab layouts
+- extension manager page
+- permission prompts
+- context menu entries
+- `tabs.*` event emission from tab model changes
+
+This should stay separate from the WebExtensions API shim. The API shim owns
+extension behavior; this UI layer only renders extension controls and prompts.
